                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, may 17: Indias foreign exchange reserves increased $200 million to $312.70 billion for the week ended May 9. The forex reserves had declined for three consecutive weeks before rising again. In the week before, forex reserves fell $371 million to $312.50 billion, according to the Reserve Bank data. Foreign currency assets during the reporting week increased $200 million to $302.77 billion.                            
	 Mumbai, may 17: Financial services major hsbc said it planned to acquire a 73.21 per cent stake in brokerage firm il amp;fs Investsmart for $241.6 million (around Rs 1,002.5 crore). The acquisition will enable hsbc to use Investsmarts platform for distribution of other financial products, including mutual funds, and help in accelerating growth of the group in the domestic market.                            
	 Mumbai, may 17: Pune-based Adurjee amp; Bros Pvt Ltd has accumulated a 7.22 per cent stake in Orchid Chemicals through open market transactions. At present, this stake is worth over Rs 125 crore.                            
	 Mumbai, may 17: An open offer by it services firm Mindtree Consulting to acquire an additional 20 per cent stake in Aztecsoft will start on June 27. The open offer will close on July 16. Earlier, the company had said the offer would start on June 30 and end on July 21.                                                                                                                         
